messages.title: Re-elect Suffolk's hardest working MP
messages.content: Labour's Sandy Martin is the hardest working MP in Suffolk. Sandy has spoken in 86 debates in Parliament over the past 2 ½ years - more than any other MP in Suffolk. Sandy and his team have spoken to 7,277 Ipswich residents and pursued 3,252 cases, on top of his wider remit. Sandy has launched two public appeals, helped funding FIND foodbank and other charities. Let's re-elect him to continue working hard for Ipswich.
